rComments: Amazing prof. Super super passionate about what she's teaching and it shows. Please make time to do her practice questions before the midterm or final. Heavily lecture based, and she points out any relevant textbook sections in her slides, so you don't need to read the entire thing. Professor Andrade; you and your spiders rock!

NOT in a million yrs I'd be able to comprehend what she is teaching! I mean when she explains a concept, it seems clear for her as her own audience but for me, it's a bunch of heavy jargons. Considering years of teaching the same course, it amazes me how she still isn't able to simplify/debunk a difficult concept to students as the MAIN audience!

Andrade is so far the best prof. I've had in the life science department. She makes learning fun by relating it to real life, her lectures make me wanna dance (so clear)!! She makes herself available to her students. She responds to questions! you won't regret a class with her. Tough exam but very good prof. so you'll be fine!
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures', 'Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Pretty good prof. The exams are fairly easy; I just go through the slides two days in advance since I skip lectures and have gotten mid-nineties on exams.

Awesome prof! Very passionate about the material and very helpful. She  provides lots of practice to help the students study and even gives marks for doing them (yup... you get marks for studying!) Her exams are very doable if you bother preparing for the exam and watch all of the lectures. Had her for two classes :D

She's very passionate when she teaches so she tends to speak really quick. Always look back at her examples as she is keen on details on her midterms/exams.  Midterms and exams are tough but the content is interesting.  Do the extra assignments to help raise your mark! Not a bird course though!
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: She's a great prof in general, and I find her lectures very interesting along with the subject. Though this was one of the lowest marks I got, I still felt like I learnt a lot from her.

rComments: For evolutionary biology, the material is not hard even if the subject bores you to sleep. Her lecture style is great, just too fast. She is incredibly helpful and likes to repeat things in lecture and on slides. Extra assignments help boost marks. Exams are a bit tricky with all of the above, none of the above answers. Not very interesting subject

She is an amazing professor and I have a lot of respect for her. Has to be one of the best profs I had. Only minus point is that she speaks very quickly in her lectures and it can be hard to keep up and her exams are a little tricky. Otherwise, I would definitely recommend her!
Excellent.
Easy marker, good explaner. Read her notes and you'll be fine.

She is clearly passionate about biology and teaching. She treasures every minute of the lecture and is open to repetition several times during office hours if a concept is challenging for an individual. Her lectures are a bit fast, but detailed enough to not need the textbook. Pay attention to her examples.
She had really clear lecture notes, memorize the examples for the term test and only use the textbook to clarify

Prof. Andrade is really a super awesome prof. She explains everything really clearly in class and if you just pay attention, all her material should come back to you quite well during studying. Go to her office hours - she's really helpful and she's interesting to talk to.

Very approachable professor. She speaks very clearly and does not have an accent. Midterm was almost all lecture based! Focus and fully understand all the examples she goes over in class! They make up almost 75% of the exam! If you know them well, you will ace the exam.
This prof was amazing. She explain everything so clearly . I loved her enthusiasm for new biology news that would occur. She used examples in order to explain a concept for us to better understand.
intense midterms and final, final was tough,  A and B B and C All of the above  None of the above those type of questions...

Dr. Andrade speaks clearly but goes fast in lectures - I suggest trying to take notes on a laptop instead of writing by hand if possible. She states expectations for the exams and mentions what specific examples she would like you to know. Her module on evolution in BIOA01 was my favourite

Dr. Andrade speaks clearly but goes fast in lectures - I suggest trying to take notes on a laptop instead of writing by hand if possible. She states expectations for the exams and mentions what specific examples she would like you to know. Her module on evolution in BIOA01 was my favourite!
lectures were great,she explains the material in a simple way so its pretty easy to understand.
Her lectures are really interesting, and she has a clear voice with no accent. Really good prof.
Everything is awesome!
Slightly repetitive, but has fascinating case studies.

Professor Andrade's amazing! She delivers informative and interesting lectures and is willing to help students to understand. Clear demonstration of knowledge with no accent. Slides well-made. Bright ideas of materials as well as teaching methods pop out. Passionate on the subject she's been studying. My favourite professor so far:)

Professor Andrade is amazing, funny, and loves bugs. However, her lectures are tedious and impossible to take notes in because she goes way too fast. Make sure to be on top of your work. She taught the evolution module and she does her research on spiders.
She's great! Very clear in what she expects of you. Her midterms can be tough, but she likes to bellcurve them up a bit anyway. I found her final much easier. I'd take more of her courses.
Awesome prof, does as much as she can to help you. Study well and you shall do well. Good looking to so, its a bonus.
she is awesome

Extremely helpful, my god. She had a review session and she got it taped! She posts FAQs and exam strategies! No other teacher at UTSC does all this. I agree her midterm was sub par. But know that she uses questions based on examples she covers in class but has very few stand-alone questions. There's at least 2 multiple choice/example.

Had her for a few classes.  She is my favourite professor at UTSC by far.  Super smart, actually cares about what she studies and how she is as a Professor, and makes lectures and projects interesting.  I recommend any class she teaches.

i couldn't agree more with the last comment.midterm was unrealistic and flawed in every way with numerous errors. class avarage as some1 already said bellcurved 20%. i understand that there needs to be a certain level of difficulty but we all need some room to breath, i belive evn if u study the least you can get is a 70%

Poorly organized exam with ridiculous expectations. Class average belled up 20% from 43 to 63. Numerous errors present on exam. Avoid her courses. It seems she doesnt take the time to write a proper exam without countless "answerless" multiple choice and flawed short answer questions.
Took 2 courses with her, fave professor. An amazing lecturer that knows how to make classes fun. Always manages to have really cool content on her lectures

If you like biology you will enjoy this course. Andrade teaches very well, and she is genuinely interested in the material. If you put in a good effort to do well, you can very easily achieve an A. The midterms and exams are very fair.

Incredible professor. Lectures are interesting and always engaging and she goes above and beyond to make sure students understand the material. I've taken two classes with her and she's still the best prof I've had.
Awesome prof, the only lecture where I'm not looking at the clock every 10 minutes. Her lectures encourages you to think for yourself, instead of memorizing like mindless ghouls.

Yes her exams were hard considering I didn't get a decent mark, but she is an awesome lecturer!! I enjoyed listening to her lectures on line, makes them interesting! She is very approachable and is willing to help her students. If you want a high mark, you must work very hard and see her for help. I believe all Bio courses are like this at U O T!!!

Good Lecturer but midterm and exams are hard. If you didn't like Mason you wont like here either. And unlike other bio teachers she doesn't bell curve up. I would definitely not recommend anyone to take her course.
love her!
My favourite Biology professor at UTSC! Makes complex concepts understandable and her lectures are extremely entertaining. Exams are fair if you understand her lectures.
horrible teacher, think shes all that, can't really teach, hard midterm, very hard.
Very long and hard midterm, you really needed to know everything in detail.
makes concepts pretty clear
talks quick, but compensated by making lectures online

This was the most amazing class I ever had, interesting material, never used the textbook, a 78 on the midterm exam and ended up with an 85 ...She is a great professor, very helpful and knowledgable ...

This class is very easy, don't even bother with the textbook (and I never say that since I usually use texts a lot). I suggest you watch her lectures online; you can make notes and such. Just study those notes, memorize the few equations you have to, and you'll do great. I got 78 on my midterm without studying more than 2 hours. Exam was easy too.
Professor Andrade is one of the best profs at UTSC. Her lectures are amazing, she's really helpful & gives practice questions for exams. Exams were tough but reasonable.
Great prof, she makes tough material relatively easy to grasp. Plus she's smokin' hot ;)
Hardest biology course I have ever taken at UTSC. A very friendly and approachable prof. who did not make the instructions on the exams clear enough. I wish they hired a different TA for this course.
A very professional, comprehensible, proficient and cool teacher! Not to mention very good looking!
Hard course, but a decent professor.

Prof.Andrade is really nice, and the exams were surprisingly harder than what I'd expected.However,I think reading the book thoroughly will really help you through the exam. The pace of lectures was okay for me because most things mentioned were already included in the lecture notes posted online.

Prof Andrade is a very fair.  Although she lectures at a very fast pace (you'd better know how to take notes very quickly), she uses tons of examples to explain concepts and such.  She's funny and very enthusiastic about what she teaches.  Interesting course for those interested in animal behaviour.

Good professor, has a lot of enthusiasm and knows her stuff. She's funny. Her lectures are very well organized, and if there's any changes, she keeps everyone updated. Just sometimes goes a bit too fast

Prof.Andrade is really nice and pleasant...but exams are tough, which is surprising given the course material. I did okay because I read the book like mad but I still found her test questions really vague and ambiguous. BAD assignment- I did horribly even though the question seemed really easy.
She goes at the right pace, considering the amount of material that needs to be covered. She also puts much time in effort into her lectures.
she explains every thing clearly. the pace is ok for me.
Brilliant - a fanatastic experience.
Explains really well in class. Very well organized. Makes really hard midterms and confusing exams.

Fabulous teacher. Very enthusiastic and knowledgable.  Explains concepts well. Funny and witty. Exams are fair. Goes off on tangents sometimes. Slides on handouts don't always follow same order as lectures.
The best professor I've ever had!!!!
She gives insanely hard exams, but props to her for giving students opportunities in her lab.
hated the whole spiders stuff...gross...but she was a good prof.
She goes by way too fast in her lecture.  She just goes on and on and on.  I have to admit...for a woman with grey hair...she sure does look pretty.
SHE is the most Sarcastic teachter on EARTH
Saw  her on tv once.
she's very quirky...lecture slides are easy to follow and study from
